========================================================================
SCIENTIFIC INTERPRETATION
========================================================================

  ► LINEAR BLEED detected. No phase takeover.
    The feedback coupling introduces measurable but bounded deviation.
    computed_mod ≠ computed, but the deviation is proportional to
    the coupling term — no nonlinear amplification observed.
    System remains classifiable as 'closed with external bias envelope'.


  KEY FINDING: r(coupling_term, computed) = 0.9685
  The coupling term is nearly identical to a scaled version of 'computed'.
  accum_reg = ∫ computed dt (time-integral over accumulation epochs).
  Feeding it back adds an ECHO of the arithmetic history — not new state info.
  This is a SELF-REINFORCING feedback, not a cross-domain coupling.

  Closure status: Arithmetic core (computed) remains UNMODIFIED.
  The coupling is a side-channel term, not a feedback loop.
  computed_mod is an OBSERVER LAYER quantity, not an architectural one.

========================================================================
BOUNDARY BETWEEN DIGITAL ARITHMETIC AND COMPUTATIONAL DYNAMICS
========================================================================

  Digital arithmetic (closed):  dynamics → accumulation only
  Computational dynamics (open): dynamics → modulate the function

  Maximum CPR observed:  0.013598
  → System is at the boundary (hybrid zone).
    CPR 1-10%: state creates a detectable arithmetic bias envelope.

